# Day 3 – Biomanufacturing & AI in Industry

## Activities
- Visited the BTEC (Biomanufacturing Training and Education Center) at NC State to learn about biomanufacturing and biotechnology.
- Explored the biomanufacturing process and learned how biological materials are used to create products such as medicines, vaccines, and other important biotechnology products.
- Learned about examples of biotechnology and biomanufacturing from NC State instructors.
- Attended a presentation by representatives from Trane Technologies about the role of artificial intelligence (AI) in modern industries.
- Learned how AI helps businesses improve efficiency, reduce energy consumption, and achieve carbon reduction goals.
- Explored BrainBox AI, an AI system that optimizes heating and air conditioning systems to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, lower costs, and improve building maintenance.
- Learned about data centers and ARIA, an AI technology used to improve operations and decision-making.

## What I Learned
Today, I learned that biomanufacturing combines biology, engineering, and technology to produce products that improve people's lives, such as medicines and vaccines. 
I gained a better understanding of how the biomanufacturing process transforms biological materials into products on a large scale. During the presentation from Trane Technologies, I learned how artificial intelligence can help companies make smarter decisions, improve employee productivity, and reduce energy usage. I also learned how BrainBox AI helps buildings become more energy efficient by optimizing heating and cooling systems, reducing greenhouse gas emissions, and lowering operating costs. Finally, I learned about the importance of data centers and how AI technologies like ARIA support businesses by processing large amounts of information efficiently.

## Favorite Part
My favorite part of the day was visiting the BTEC facility because it was exciting to see how biotechnology is applied in real-world manufacturing. 
I also enjoyed learning about how AI is being used to create smarter, more sustainable buildings. Seeing how technologies like BrainBox AI can reduce energy use while helping the environment showed me how AI can make a positive impact on society.
